  <title>Delete a Host Group</title>
  <shortdesc>You can delete a host group when it is no longer needed. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_212840F69CDF4BB5B316F6577CD380E0">
      <p>
        <note>You cannot delete the Production host group (usually the
			 production host), but you can rename it. 
		  </note>
      </p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_F2B915F4C83C4FC0B857D33F796297E7">
      <step id="step_0AD2BD6DB9A34A2A96B4A8FE51A02FD7">
        <cmd>In the Host Group Administration page, click the delete button for
			 your host group. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
